{{if .Backpressure}}## Burpvalve Gate Choreography

- Stage only the files owned by the current atomic payload. If the index already contains unrelated staged paths, resolve ownership before running the gate.
- Run the verifier/gate against the staged slice, keep responses honest and bound to the current payload, and never use bypass flags to force a commit through.
- If the gate writes an attestation, stage exactly that generated artifact with the payload and rerun the commit so history contains the evidence it validated.
- Treat failures, unknown verdicts, and verifier disagreements as blockers until resolved. Do not rewrite verifier findings to fit the desired outcome.

## Verifier Work

- Verifiers are read-only reviewers for the exact staged payload and condition cell they are assigned.
- Verdicts need concrete evidence. Authorization to request verification is never evidence that a condition passed.
- Preserve each verifier's actual verdict, provenance, and evidence. If two trusted verifiers disagree, hold the commit and escalate instead of choosing the convenient answer.

{{end}}
{{if .NTM}}## NTM Session Naming

Use the repo basename as the base session name. Use labels only for variants:

- Base session: `<repo-name>`
- Labeled session: `<repo-name>--frontend`
- Labeled session: `<repo-name>--backend`

Before state-changing NTM commands, check `ntm --robot-capabilities` and verify state with `ntm --robot-snapshot`.

NTM is an optional top-level coordination bridge, not the default verifier fanout for feature x condition cells. If you use NTM, keep reviewer/coordinator swarms small (2-10 agents), preserve per-cell evidence{{if .Docs}}, and follow `/docs/ntm-bridge.md`{{end}}.

{{end}}{{if .Verifier}}## Verifier Orchestration

Standing verifier authorization permits spawning read-only verifier subagents for backpressure checks. It is never per-cell evidence. Every feature x condition cell still needs real verifier output, provenance, and evidence for the current staged payload. Do not fabricate subagent confirmation.

{{end}}{{if .Backpressure}}## Backpressure

Backpressure rules live in `/backpressure/`. A task is not done because an agent says it is done; it is done when the relevant checks have accepted the artifact or the blocker is explicit.

Before committing feature work, run the backpressure verifier. The verifier must confirm every active backpressure condition for every changed feature, or attach a failure/blocker message for each unmet condition.

{{end}}## Definition Of Done

- Relevant checks run and results recorded.
{{if .Backpressure}}- Backpressure verifier has a complete feature x condition matrix.
{{end}}{{if .Beads}}- Bead closed or blocker recorded.
{{end}}- Files committed when appropriate.
- Remaining risks or follow-ups named.

